ðŸ§  3. Java Memory Model (JMM)

The Java Memory Model defines how threads interact through memory, including:
   * What a thread is allowed to see from other threads
   * When writes become visible
   * Which operations are atomic
   * What reordering the JVM is allowed to do
   * What the volatile keyword actually means
   * Why correct thread-safety requires happens-before relationships

